cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.FL, cs.CC 

This paper deals with the connection between higher-order recursion schemes and intersection type systems, which are topics related to logic and programming languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses linear logic, which is a subfield of cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper involves automata theory, which is related to cs.LG (Computational Geometry). The paper also mentions model-checking, which is a topic in cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
